#AUTHORS : Prarthit Mehra and Mohan Gupta

<-><-><-><-><-><-><-><-><-><-><-><-><-><-><-><-><->

The purpose of this application is to create an interactive screen saver, which simulates collisions
in 3D, allowing users to increase/decrease speed, pause/resume etc using one to one thread communication.

<-><-><-><-><-><-><-><-><-><-><-><-><-><-><-><-><->

REQUIREMENTS : The following libraries are required in your pc for this project to work properly.

-OpenGL
-Freeglut
-pthread

The version of g++ required to compile c++11

<-><-><-><-><-><-><-><-><-><-><-><-><-><-><-><-><->

HOW TO COMPILE AND EXECUTE?

1.> Extract the repository
2.> After extracting there will be a folder created named Screen-Saver3.> Open the folder and go to Code folder and then right click anywhere inside folder and select open terminal here option 
4.> Type "make" without quotations and hit enter to run the project

<-><-><-><-><-><-><-><-><-><-><-><-><-><-><-><-><->

EXTRA FEATURES :

Initially if you type make alone, by default there are 5 balls set. But you can run the project using your own desired no of balls
by just changing (4th) step in how to compile and execute to "make num_thread=x" without quotations where x is the number of balls
you want.

The following is list of keyboard options available :
	-> [+/-] : To increase/decrease speed of ball
	-> [Spacebar] : To pause/play the animation
	-> [ESC] : To exit the program
	-> [Up/Down] : To go inside and come out of cube
	-> [F5] : For viewing in fullscreen
	-> [F4] : For going back to normal mode from fullscreen mode

